      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[AI-assisted] Preserve thread sessions across daily reset by default",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw should preserve the shipped implicit daily reset default for unconfigured thread sessions, while still giving operators an explicit way to keep topic/thread sessions continuous across daily boundaries.\n\nThere is also a closed-thread rollover bug for explicit idle/no-expiry thread policies: the Discord archived-thread helper previously marked sessions stale by zeroing `updatedAt`, but an idle/no-expiry policy has no idle deadline, so a later message can still reuse the closed thread session.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Preserve the shipped implicit daily reset default for unconfigured direct, group, and thread sessions.\n- Document explicit topic/thread continuity with `session.resetByType.thread: { mode: \"idle\", idleMinutes: 0 }`.\n- Add durable `sessionClosedAt` session-store state for closed thread sessions.\n- Propagate `sessionClosedAt` through session freshness evaluation so closed sessions roll over even when idle expiry is disabled.\n- Preserve the closed marker through system-event writes and clear it when a real user turn rolls into a fresh session.\n\n## Evidence\n\nValidation:\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/config/sessions/sessions.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts`\n  - 2 test files passed\n  - 168 tests passed\n- `git diff --check`\n  - passed\n\nCurrent-head follow-up validation after sibling-path fix:\n\n- **Current PR head tested:** `7b2cab7ec3`\n- **Fix covered:** gateway and command-session rollover writers now clear `sessionClosedAt` when they mint a fresh `sessionId`, preventing repeated rollovers on the next turn.\n- **Focused acceptance command:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/server-methods/agent.test.ts src/agents/command/session-store.test.ts src/config/sessions/sessions.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts`\n  - 4 Vitest shards passed\n  - 546 tests passed\n- **Whitespace check:** `git diff --check` passed\n\nCurrent-head real behavior proof before the sibling-path marker-clear follow-up:\n\n- **Current PR head tested:** `f53724f2ca59`\n- **Runtime path tested:** real `initSessionState()` from this PR branch via `pnpm exec tsx --eval`.\n- **Environment/data:** local clean checkout with temporary `sessions.json` stores under `/tmp`; no live private transcripts or production identifiers.\n- **What the proof covers:** final default-preserving behavior, explicit idle/no-expiry thread continuity, and Discord closed-thread rollover via `sessionClosedAt`.\n\nTerminal output from the current-head proof command:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"f53724f2ca59\",\n  \"tempRoot\": \"openclaw-pr90226-proof-d7gIej\",\n  \"observations\": {\n    \"unconfiguredThreadDailyDefault\": {\n      \"previousSessionId\": \"daily-before-boundary\",\n      \"isNewSession\": true,\n      \"reusedPrevious\": false,\n      \"resetTriggered\": false\n    },\n    \"explicitThreadIdleNoExpiry\": {\n      \"previousSessionId\": \"explicit-idle-before-boundary\",\n      \"isNewSession\": false,\n      \"reusedPrevious\": true,\n      \"resetTriggered\": false\n    },\n    \"closedDiscordThreadRollover\": {\n      \"previousSessionId\": \"closed-discord-before-rollover\",\n      \"isNewSession\": true,\n      \"reusedPrevious\": false,\n      \"previousEntryHadClosedAt\": true,\n      \"newEntryClosedAt\": null,\n      \"archivedTranscriptCreated\": true,\n      \"activeTranscriptStillPresent\": false\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nObserved result:\n\n- Unconfigured thread sessions still roll over after the daily boundary, preserving shipped default behavior.\n- Explicit `resetByType.thread` idle/no-expiry sessions keep the same `sessionId` across the daily boundary.\n- A Discord thread session marked with `sessionClosedAt` creates a fresh session on the next user message, archives the old transcript, and clears the closed marker from the new session entry.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a live Discord or Telegram bot conversation in production. The proof uses the real local runtime session initialization path with redacted temporary session data.\n",
